    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Grounds and complexes designed to educate visitors about animals, plants, weather, and the environment, often including structures for educational activities and outdoor grounds containing native plant communities, wildlife habitats, walking trails, and other facilities.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050737/Evans and Evans, Nature Center Book (2004)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>用來教育參觀者有關動物、植物、氣候和環境等議題的場地與複合建築，通常包括教育活動使用之建築物，以及容納原生植物群落、野生動物棲息地、步道和其他設施的戶外空間。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
